<Coders>


1. Availability for meeting expectations: Monday and Friday meetings: 8pm. Roughly an hour meeting. First strike talk about at the next meeting, second strike bring up to TA. Shouldn't be later than 20 minutes.
Phone usage doesn't matter as long as your listening, food and drink doesn't matter.

2. Response time to communication expectations: For official responses regarding the project, all members must reply within 24 hours on the discord general chat. 

3. Definition of done: when is a task complete? (hint: "I'm done with that but I didn't check it in to github" is not done.)
When a pull request is reviewed and merged to main it is done.

4. Scrum meeting format/frequency and distribution of documentation tasks (meeting minutes, updating task board)
  Meeting Format: Each person should talk about the tasks they are working on/completed for this week, person should talk about what tasks they are signing
  up for this week, provide simple feedback on what has been completed/inprogress, Q/A.
  Meeting Minutes: Nathan Edwards
  Update Task Board (Weekly Rotation): Matt, Rory, Nathan, Andy

5. Procedure for adopting policies (e.g. code style, code check-in steps, documentation updates)
if you adopt such a policy during the initial meeting, put it here: 2 members must approve pull request and must provide a comment on something good/or needs improvement, lowercase, 

6. Procedure for handling a member who is not meeting expectations must include at least 3 actions before involving the instructor: Send an email, talk to him at the next meeting, or send a message directly to him, Discord: https://discord.gg/eezkWpsT 
